# Oral History Metadata Guide

Metadata helps future generations understand what an interview contains, where it came from, and how it may be used.

## Core fields

- `interview_id`: Unique ID for the interview, e.g. `PB-OH-001`
- `interviewee_full_name`: Full name of the person interviewed
- `preferred_public_name`: Name the interviewee wants displayed publicly
- `community_or_island_connection`: Pulau Brani, Pulau Semakau, Southern Islands, Orang Laut, Orang Pulau, etc.
- `date_of_interview`: Date the interview was conducted
- `location_of_interview`: Place of interview
- `interviewer`: Name of interviewer
- `language_or_dialect`: Language or dialect used
- `recording_format`: Audio, video, written notes, photographs

## Consent and permissions

- `permission_public_use`: Whether the interview may be shared publicly
- `permission_ai_transcription`: Whether AI tools may be used to transcribe
- `permission_translation`: Whether the interview may be translated
- `permission_photos_or_objects`: Whether related photos or objects may be documented
- `usage_restrictions`: Any limits requested by the interviewee or family

## Description fields

- `key_topics`: Main themes discussed
- `people_mentioned`: Family members, elders, neighbours, community figures
- `places_mentioned`: Islands, villages, jetties, mosques, graves, beaches, routes
- `rituals_or_festivals_mentioned`: Hari Raya, Malam Tujuh Likur, weddings, kenduri, funerals
- `foodways_mentioned`: Dishes, recipes, fishing, foraging, cooking practices
- `maritime_knowledge_mentioned`: Tides, boats, fishing methods, routes, taboos, sea knowledge
- `related_photos_or_objects`: Any family archives, photographs, tools, documents, or objects mentioned

## Review fields

- `review_status`: Pending, reviewed, restricted, approved for public use
- `reviewed_by`: Person who reviewed the material
- `date_reviewed`: Date of review
- `notes`: Any additional context
